<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_2a10fb16-4521-421f-81c0-f10f2a6f8650" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/></meta><sptc>10.2.17</sptc><title id="_9b23d1dc-aaf5-43c2-9b66-d9820d65656a">Enclosed showers with level threshold (without hob or set down)</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_ee10b3ec-ba96-4d0d-a91a-fdf489c878fa" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_c22626b0-62fc-46a8-b921-a3226154c451">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>For enclosed showers without a stepdown or a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4660_0.4.0.xml#_6daa7d7f-9147-4c10-98bc-c3cee9774bdb" id="_f92958fc-3f11-47c2-b40c-63c93d093377" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">hob</xref>, at the extremity of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1460_0.12.0.xml#_6aa99639-a955-4628-bc59-dabb3bfc8118" id="_d4c91230-5f8c-4afe-80ee-247851a965ea" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">shower area</xref>, a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4735_0.5.0.xml#_2fb1baed-5210-4b6f-a0d1-49efc309b967" id="_28d584a9-23a4-40db-8782-7e6c8c0c5822" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterstop</xref> must be positioned so that its vertical leg finishes—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_2697ff51-7585-4d55-ae5c-281df587837e">where a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4663_0.4.0.xml#_013ce393-1153-476d-b268-5b06c64f9232" id="_f684edab-b55a-4756-b893-dd2753ba2c8d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">shower screen</xref> is to be installed, not less than 5 mm above the finished floor level (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4733_0.18.0.xml#_16951e0a-f0ae-4ee1-ab26-02b21b3cdb95" id="_b554a7b4-af94-4928-90da-7a38ff6c9559" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 10.2.17</xref>); and</li><li id="_b34d2c44-e998-4199-98fa-4b5ffefa4ed2">where the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4735_0.5.0.xml#_2fb1baed-5210-4b6f-a0d1-49efc309b967" id="_254a95c7-b861-4695-bcc1-f12352654902" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterstop</xref> intersects with a wall or has a joint, the junction must be waterproof.</li></ol></subclause><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4733_0.18.0.xml" id="_16951e0a-f0ae-4ee1-ab26-02b21b3cdb95"><num/><title id="_12eaf1fc-a1f0-410e-ba87-980330ced661"/></image-reference></clause>